📄 Project Report – Professional Email & Etiquette Guide
For this task, I created a guide on writing professional emails and maintaining proper email etiquette using tools like Canva and Gmail.
The guide focuses on helping students communicate effectively in academic and professional environments.
My design explains the structure of a professional email, including a clear subject line, proper greeting, concise body, and polite closing. 
It also highlights important etiquette rules such as using formal language, avoiding slang, checking grammar, and responding on time.
I included examples to show the difference between informal and professional emails.
This guide demonstrates the importance of respectful and clear communication in digital platforms. 
It helps students create a positive impression while interacting with teachers, employers, or organizations.
The most interesting part was designing the layout and choosing appropriate examples.
The challenging part was keeping the content short yet informative.
Overall, this task improved my communication skills and taught me how to write effective professional emails.
